article_title: Wayward Dolphin Found in Coney Island Creek
article_text:
A wayward dolphin found its way into the Coney Island Creek on Thursday morning, New York City police said.

Kevin Hagen for The Wall Street Journal

The dolphin was spotted around 10:30 a.m. swimming in shallow water by a bridge near Cropsey Avenue and Bay 54th Street. As of Thursday afternoon, the dolphin was not considered to be in danger, police said.

Kevin Hagen for The Wall Street Journal

Police were advised by marine biologists to let the dolphin finds it way back out to sea during high tide, which is scheduled for late afternoon.

Kevin Hagen for The Wall Street Journal

Carla Mosso, 11, Emily Colindrez, 26, Areli Mosso, 9, and Mia Reyes, 6, tried to get a glimpse of the dolphin on Thursday.

In January, a dolphin swam into the Gowanus Canal and later died.

Kevin Hagen for The Wall Street Journal

Lt. Barry Duignan spoke to the press about the NYPD Emergency Services Unit’s response to the dolphin.
